obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE MAHATMA GANDHI ANTARRASHTRIYA HINDI VISHWAVIDYALAYA ACT, 1996`
  line `A CT N O. 3 OF 1997`
  line `[8 th January, 1997.]`
  line `An Act to establish and incorporate a teaching University for the promotion and development of`
  line `Hindi language and literature, through teaching and research, with a view to enabling Hindi`
  line `to achieve greater functional efficiency and recognition as a major international language and`
  line `to provide for matters connected therewith or incidental thereto.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Forty-seventh Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Mahatma Gandhi Antarrashtriya`
  line `Hindi Vishwavidyalaya Act, 1996.`
  line `( 2 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, and the Statutes made hereunder, unless the context otherwise`
  line `requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ Academic Council ” means the Academic Council of the University;`
  line `( b ) “ academic staff ” means such categories of staff as are designated as academic staff by the`
  line Ordinances;
  line `( c ) “ Board of Studies ” means the Board of Studies of the University;`
  line `( d ) “ Chancellor ”, “ Vice-Chancellor ” and Pro-Vice-Chancellor ” mean, respectively, the`
  line `Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor and Pro-Vice-Chancellor of the University;`
  line `( e ) “ Court ” means the Court of the University;`
  line `( f ) “ Department ” means a Department of Studies and includes a Centre of Studies;`
  line `( g ) “ distance education system ” means the system of imparting education through any means of`
  line `communication, such as broadcasting, telecasting, correspondence courses, seminars, contact`
  line `programmes or the combination of any two or more such means;`
  line `( h ) “ employee ” means any person appointed by the University, and includes teachers and other`
  line `staff of the University;`
  line `( i ) “ Executive Council ” means the Executive Council of the University;`
  line `( j ) “ Finance Committee ” means the Finance Committee of the University;`
  line `( k ) “ Hall ” means a unit of residence or of corporate life for the students of the University, or of an`
  line `Institution maintained by the University;`
  line `( l ) “ Institution ” means an academic institution, not being a College, maintained by the University;`
  line `( m ) “ recognised Institution ” means an institution of higher learning recognised by the University;`
  line `( n ) “ Regulations ” means the Regulations made by any authority of the University under this Act`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line `1. 29th December, 1997, vide notification No. S.O. 912(E), dated 29th November, 1997, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3( ii ).`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( o ) “ School ” means a School of Studies of the University;`
  line `( p ) “ Statutes ” and “ Ordinances ” mean, respectively, the Statutes and Ordinances of the University`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line `( q ) “ teachers of the University ” means Professors, Readers, Lecturers and such other persons as`
  line `may be appointed for imparting instruction or conducting research in the University or in any`
  line `Institution maintained by the University and are designated as teachers by the Ordinances;`
  line `( r ) “ University ” means the Mahatma Gandhi Antarrashtriya Hindi Vishwavidyalaya established`
  line `and incorporated as a University under this Act.`
  line `3. Establishment of the University. — ( 1 ) There shall be established a University by the name of`
  line `“ Mahatma Gandhi Antarrashtriya Hindi Vishwavidyalaya ”.`
  line `( 2 ) The headquarters of the University shall be at Wardha.`
  line `( 3 ) The first Chancellor and the first Vice-Chancellor and the first members of the Court, the`
  line `Executive Council and the Academic Council and all persons who may hereafter become such officers or`
  line `members, so long as they continue to hold such office or membership, are hereby constituted a body`
  line `corporate by the name of “ Mahatma Gandhi Antarrashtriya Hindi Vishwavidyalaya ”.`
  line `( 4 ) The University shall have perpetual succession and a common seal and shall sue and be sued by`
  line `the said name.`
  line `4. Objects of the University. — The objects of the University shall be to promote and develop Hindi`
  line `language and literature in general and, for that purpose, to provide for instructional and research facilities`
  line `in the relevant branches of learning; to provide for active pursuit of comparative studies and research in`
  line `Hindi and other Indian languages; to create facilities for development and dissemination of relevant`
  line `information in the country and abroad; to offer programmes of Research, Education and Training in areas`
  line `like translation, interpretation and linguistics for improving the functional effectiveness of Hindi; to reach`
  line `out to Hindi scholars and groups interested in Hindi abroad and to associate them in teaching and research`
  line `and to popularize Hindi through distance education system.`
  line `5. Powers of the University. — The University shall have the following powers, namely: —`
  line `( i ) to provide for instructions in the relevant branches of learning and to make provision for the`
  line `advancement and dissemination of knowledge for furtherance of its objects;`
  line `( ii ) to grant, subject to such conditions as the University may determine, diplomas or certificates`
  line `to, and confer degrees or other academic distinctions on the basis of examinations, evaluation or any`
  line `other method of testing on, persons, and to withdraw any such diplomas, certificates, degrees or other`
  line `academic distinctions for good and sufficient cause;`
  line `( iii ) to organise and to undertake extra-mural studies, training and extension services;`
  line `( iv ) to confer honorary degrees or other distinctions in the manner prescribed by the Statutes;`
  line `( v ) to provide for facilities through distance education system to such persons as it may`
  line determine;
  line `( vi ) to institute Professorships, Readerships, Lecturerships and other teaching or academic`
  line `positions, required by the University and to appoint persons to such Professorships, Readerships,`
  line `Lecturerships or other teaching or academic positions;`
  line `( vii ) to recognise, with the prior approval of the Visitor, an institution of higher learning, within`
  line `or outside India for such purposes as the University may determine and to withdraw such recognition;`
  line `( viii ) to appoint persons working in any other University or organisation as teacher of the`
  line `University for a specified period;`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( ix ) to create administrative, ministerial and other posts and to make appointments thereto;`
  line `( x ) to co-operate or collaborate or associate with any other University or authority or institution of`
  line `higher learning in such manner and for such purposes as the University may determine;`
  line `( xi ) to establish, with the prior approval of the Visitor, such campuses, special centres and`
  line `specialised laboratories, within or outside India, as are, in the opinion of the University, necessary for`
  line `the furtherance of its objects;`
  line `( xii ) to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line `( xiii ) to establish and maintain Institutions and Halls;`
  line `( xiv ) to make provision for research and advisory services and for that purpose to enter into such`
  line `arrangements with other institutions, industrial or other organisations, as the University may deem`
  line necessary;
  line `( xv ) to organise and conduct refresher courses, workshops, seminars and other programmes for`
  line `teachers, evaluators and other academic staff;`
  line `( xvi ) to make special arrangements in respect of the residence, discipline and teaching of women`
  line `students as the University may consider desirable;`
  line `( xvii ) to appoint on contract or otherwise visiting Professors, Emeritus Professors, Consultants,`
  line `Scholars and such other persons who may contribute to the advancement of the objects of the`
  line University;
  line `( xviii ) to confer autonomous status on a Department, in accordance with the Statutes;`
  line `( xix ) to determine standards of admission to the University, which may include examination,`
  line `evaluation or any other method of testing;`
  line `( xx ) to demand and receive payment of fees and other charges;`
  line `( xxi ) to supervise the residences of the students of the University and to make arrangements for`
  line `promoting their health and general welfare;`
  line `( xxii ) to lay down conditions of service of all categories of employees, including their code of`
  line conduct;
  line `( xxiii ) to regulate and enforce discipline among the students and the employees, and to take such`
  line `disciplinary measures in this regard as may be deemed by the University to be necessary;`
  line `( xxiv ) to make arrangements for promoting the health and general welfare of the employees;`
  line `( xxv ) to receive benefactions, donations and gifts and to acquire, hold, manage and dispose of any`
  line `property, movable or immovable, including trust and endowment properties for the purposes of the`
  line University;
  line `( xxvi ) to borrow, with the approval of the Central Government, on the security of the property of`
  line `the University, money for the purposes of the University;`
  line `( xxvii ) to do all such other acts and things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the`
  line `attainment of all or any of its objects.`
  line `6. Jurisdiction. — The jurisdiction of the University shall extend to the whole of India.`
  line `7. University open to all classes, castes and creeds. — The University shall be open to persons of`
  line `either sex and of whatever caste, creed, race or class, and it shall not be lawful for the University to adopt`
  line `or impose on any person, any test whatsoever of religious belief or profession in order to entitle him to be`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `appointed as a teacher of the University or to hold any other office therein or to be admitted as a student`
  line `in the University or to graduate thereat or to enjoy or exercise any privilege thereof:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent the University from making special`
  line `provisions for the employment or admission of women, physically handicapped or of persons belonging`
  line `to the weaker sections of the society and, in particular, of the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line `8. Residence of students. — The University shall, primarily, be a residential University:`
  line `Provided that the requirements of residence shall be regulated in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Ordinances.`
  line `9. The Visitor. — ( 1 ) The President of India shall be the Visitor of the University.`
  line `( 2 ) The Visitor may, from time to time, appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress`
  line `of the University, including any Institution managed by it, and to submit a report thereon; and upon`
  line `receipt of that report the Visitor may, after obtaining the views of the Executive Council thereon through`
  line `the Vice-Chancellor, take such action and issue such directions as he considers necessary in respect of`
  line `any of the matters dealt with in the report and the University shall be bound to comply with such`
  line directions.
  line `( 3 ) The Visitor shall have the right to cause an inspection to be made by such person or persons as he`
  line `may direct, of the University, its buildings, laboratories and equipment and of an Institution and also of`
  line `the examinations, teaching and other work conducted or done by the University and to cause an inquiry to`
  line `be made in like manner in respect of any matter connected with the administration or finances of the`
  line `University or Institutions.`
  line `( 4 ) The Visitor shall, in every matter referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), give notice of his intention to`
  line `cause an inspection or inquiry to be made to the University and the University shall have the right to`
  line `make such representations to the Visitor, as it may consider necessary.`
  line `( 5 ) After considering the representations, if any, made by the University, the Visitor may cause to be`
  line `made such inspection or inquiry as is referred to in sub-section ( 3 ).`
  line `( 6 ) Where any inspection or inquiry has been caused to be made by the Visitor, the University shall`
  line `be entitled to appoint a representative, who shall have the right to be present and be heard at such`
  line `inspection or inquiry.`
  line `( 7 ) The Visitor may, if the inspection or inquiry is made in respect of the University or any Institution`
  line `address the Vice-Chancellor with reference to the result of such inspection or inquiry together with such`
  line `views and advice with regard to the action to be taken thereon, as the Visitor may be pleased to offer, and`
  line `on receipt of address made by the Visitor, the Vice-Chancellor shall communicate to the Executive`
  line `Council, the views of the Visitor with such advice as the Visitor may offer upon the action to be taken`
  line thereon.
  line `( 8 ) The Executive Council shall communicate, through the Vice-Chancellor, to the Visitor such`
  line `action, if any, as it proposes to take or has been taken upon the result of such inspection or inquiry.`
  line `( 9 ) Where, the Executive Council does not, within a reasonable time, take action to the satisfaction of`
  line `the Visitor, the Visitor may, after considering any explanation furnished or representation made by the`
  line `Executive Council, issue such directions as he may think fit and the Executive Council shall comply with`
  line `such directions.`
  line `( 10 ) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section, the Visitor may, by order in`
  line `writing, annul any proceeding of the University which is not in conformity with this Act, the Statutes or`
  line `the Ordinances:`
  line `Provided that before making any such order, he shall call upon the Registrar to show cause why such`
  line `an order should not be made, and, if any cause is shown within a reasonable time, he shall consider the`
  line same.
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `( 11 ) The Visitor shall have such other powers as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `10. Officers of the University. — The following shall be the officers of the University: —`
  line `( 1 ) the Chancellor;`
  line `( 2 ) the Vice-Chancellor;`
  line `( 3 ) the Pro-Vice-Chancellor;`
  line `( 4 ) the Deans of Schools;`
  line `( 5 ) the Registrar;`
  line `( 6 ) the Finance Officer;`
  line `( 7 ) the Librarian; and`
  line `( 8 ) such other officers as may be declared by the Statutes to be officers of the University.`
  line `11. The Chancellor. — ( 1 ) The Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `( 2 ) The Chancellor shall, by virtue of his office, be the head of the University.`
  line `( 3 ) The Chancellor shall, if present, preside at the convocation of the University held for conferring`
  line `degrees and the meetings of the Court.`
  line `12. The Vice-Chancellor. — ( 1 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor in such`
  line `manner and on such terms and conditions of service as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `( 2 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be the principal executive and academic officer of the University and`
  line `shall exercise general supervision and control over the affairs of the University and give effect to the`
  line `decisions of all the authorities of the University.`
  line `( 3 ) The Vice-Chancellor may, if he is of opinion that immediate action is necessary on any matter,`
  line `exercise any power conferred on any authority of the University by or under this Act and shall report to`
  line `such authority the action taken by him on such matters:`
  line `Provided that if the authority concerned is of opinion that such action ought not to have been taken, it`
  line `may refer the matter to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be final:`
  line `Provided further that any person in the service of the University who is aggrieved by the action taken`
  line `by the Vice-Chancellor under this sub-section shall have the right to appeal against such action to the`
  line `Executive Council within three months from the date on which decision on such action is communicated`
  line `to him and thereupon the Executive Council may confirm, modify or reverse the action taken by the Vice-`
  line Chancellor.
  line `( 4 ) The Vice-Chancellor, if he is of the opinion that any decision of any authority of the University is`
  line `beyond the powers of the authority conferred by the provisions of this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances`
  line `or that any decision taken is not in the interest of the University, may ask the authority concerned to`
  line `review its decision within sixty days of such decision and if the authority refuses to review the decision`
  line `either in whole or in part or no decision is taken by it within the said period of sixty days, the matter shall`
  line `be referred to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line `( 5 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
  line `13. The Pro-Vice-Chancellor. — The Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed in such manner and`
  line `shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `14. The Deans of Schools. — Every Dean of a School shall be appointed in such manner and shall`
  line `exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `15. The Registrar. — ( 1 ) The Registrar shall be appointed in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line Statutes.
  line `( 2 ) The Registrar shall have the power to enter into agreement, sign documents and authenticate`
  line `records on behalf of the University and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `16. The Finance Officer. — The Finance Officer shall be appointed in such manner and shall exercise`
  line `such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `17. The Librarian. — The Librarian shall be appointed in such manner and shall exercise such powers`
  line `and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `18. Other officers. — The manner of appointment and powers and duties of the other officers of the`
  line `University shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `19. Authorities of the University. — The following shall be the authorities of the University: —`
  line `( 1 ) the Court;`
  line `( 2 ) the Executive Council;`
  line `( 3 ) the Academic Council;`
  line `( 4 ) the Board of Studies;`
  line `( 5 ) the Finance Committee; and`
  line `( 6 ) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the`
  line University.
  line `20. The Court. — ( 1 ) The constitution of the Court and the term of office of its members shall be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Court shall have the following powers and functions,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) to review, from time to time, the broad policies and programmes of the University and to`
  line `suggest measures for the improvement and development of the University;`
  line `( b ) to advise the Visitor in respect of any matter which may be referred to it for advice; and`
  line `( c ) to perform such other functions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `21. The Executive Council. — ( 1 ) The Executive Council shall be the principal executive body of the`
  line University.
  line `( 2 ) The constitution of the Executive Council, the term of office of its members and its powers and`
  line `functions shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `22. The Academic Council. — ( 1 ) The Academic Council shall be the principal academic body of the`
  line `University and shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, exercise`
  line `general supervision over the academic policies of the University.`
  line `( 2 ) The constitution of the Academic Council, the term of office of its members and its powers and`
  line `functions shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `23. The Board of Studies. — The constitution, powers and functions of the Board of Studies shall be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `24. The Finance Committee. — The constitution, powers and functions of the Finance Committee`
  line `shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `25. Other authorities of the University. — The constitution, powers and functions of other`
  line `authorities, as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the University, shall be prescribed`
  line `by the Statutes.`
  line `26. Power to make Statutes. — Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the constitution, powers and functions of the authorities and other bodies of the University, as`
  line `may be constituted from time to time;`
  line `( b ) the appointment and continuance in office of the members of the said authorities and bodies,`
  line `filling up of vacancies of members and all other matters relating to those authorities and other bodies`
  line `for which it may be necessary or desirable to provide;`
  line `( c ) the appointment, powers and duties of the officers of the University and their emoluments;`
  line `( d ) the appointment of teachers, academic staff and other employees of the University, their`
  line `emoluments and other conditions of service;`
  line `( e ) the appointment of teachers and academic staff working in any other University or`
  line `organisation for specific period for undertaking a joint project;`
  line `( f ) the conditions of service of employees including provision for pension, insurance and`
  line `provident fund, the manner of termination of service and disciplinary action;`
  line `( g ) the principles governing the seniority of service of the employees of the University;`
  line `( h ) the procedure for arbitration in cases of dispute between employees or students and the`
  line University;
  line `( i ) the procedure for appeal to the Executive Council by any employee or student against the`
  line `action of any officer or authority of the University;`
  line `( j ) the conferment of autonomous status on an Institution or a Department;`
  line `( k ) the establishment and abolition of Schools, Departments, Centres, Halls and Institutions;`
  line `( l ) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line `( m ) the withdrawal of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions;`
  line `( n ) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line `( o ) the delegation of powers vested in the authorities or officers of the University;`
  line `( p ) the maintenance of discipline among the employees and students;`
  line `( q ) all other matters which by this Act are to be or may be provided for by the Statutes.`
  line `27. Statutes how to be made. — ( 1 ) The first Statutes are those set out in the Schedule.`
  line `( 2 ) The Executive Council may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or`
  line `repeal the Statutes referred to in sub-section ( 1 ):`
  line `Provided that the Executive Council shall not make, amend or repeal any Statutes affecting the status,`
  line `powers or constitution of any authority of the University until such authority has been given an`
  line `opportunity of expressing an opinion in writing on the proposed changes and any opinion so expressed`
  line `shall be considered by the Executive Council:`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `Provided further that the Executive Council shall not consider to make, amend or repeal any Statute`
  line `relating to the matters provided under clauses ( j ) and ( k ) of section 26 except with the prior approval of`
  line `the Visitor.`
  line `( 3 ) Every new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall require`
  line `the assent of the Visitor who may assent thereto or withhold assent or remit to the Executive Council for`
  line re-consideration.
  line `( 4 ) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless`
  line `it has been assented to by the Visitor.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub- sections, the Visitor may make new or`
  line `additional Statutes or amend or repeal the Statutes referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), during the period of three`
  line `years immediately after the commencement of this Act:`
  line `Provided that the Visitor may, on the expiry of the said period of three years, make, within one year`
  line `from the date of such expiry, such detailed Statutes as he may consider necessary and such detailed`
  line `Statutes shall be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, the Visitor may direct the`
  line `University to make provisions in the Statutes in respect of any matter specified by him and if the`
  line `Executive Council is unable to implement such direction within sixty days of its receipt, the Visitor may,`
  line `after considering the reasons, if any, communicated by the Executive Council for its inability to comply`
  line `with such direction, make or amend the Statutes suitably.`
  line `28. Power to make Ordinances. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the`
  line `Ordinances may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the admission of students to the University and their enrolment as such;`
  line `( b ) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and certificates of the`
  line University;
  line `( c ) the medium of instruction and examination;`
  line `( d ) the award of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions, qualifications for`
  line `the same and the means to be taken relating to the granting and obtaining of the same;`
  line `( e ) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the University and for admission to the`
  line `examinations, degrees and diplomas of the University;`
  line `( f ) the conditions for award of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line `( g ) the conduct of examinations, including the term of office and manner of appointment and the`
  line `duties of examining bodies, examiners and moderators;`
  line `( h ) the conditions of residence of the students of the University;`
  line `( i ) the special arrangements, if any, which may be made for the residence, discipline and teaching`
  line `of women students and prescribing of special courses of studies for them;`
  line `( j ) the appointments and emoluments of employees other than those for whom provision has been`
  line `made in the Statutes;`
  line `( k ) the establishment of Centres of Studies, Board of Studies, Special Centres, Specialised`
  line `Laboratories and other Committees;`
  line `( l ) the manner of co-operation and collaboration with other Universities, Institutions and other`
  line `agencies including learned bodies or associations in India or abroad;`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `( m ) the creation, composition and functions of any other body which is considered necessary for`
  line `improving the academic life of the University;`
  line `( n ) such other terms and conditions of service of teachers and other academic staff as are not`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes;`
  line `( o ) the management of Institutions established by the University;`
  line `( p ) setting up of a machinery for redressal of grievances of employees; and`
  line `( q ) all other matters which, by this Act or the Statutes, are to be or may be, provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
  line `( 2 ) The first Ordinances shall be made by the Vice-Chancellor with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and the Ordinances so made may be amended, repealed or added to at any time by`
  line `the Executive Council in the manner prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `29. Regulations. — The authorities of the University may make Regulations, consistent with this Act,`
  line `the Statutes and the Ordinances for the conduct of their own business and that of the Committees, if any,`
  line `appointed by them and not provided for by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances, in the manner`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `30. Annual report. — ( 1 ) The annual report of the University shall be prepared under the direction of`
  line `the Executive Council which shall include, among other matters, the steps taken by the University`
  line `towards the fulfilment of its objects, and shall be submitted to the Visitor on or before such date as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `( 2 ) A copy of the annual report, as prepared under sub-section ( 1 ) shall also be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.
  line `31. Annual accounts. — ( 1 ) The annual accounts and balance-sheet of the University shall be`
  line `prepared under the directions of the Executive Council and shall, once at least every year and at intervals`
  line `of not more than fifteen months, be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or by such`
  line `persons as he may authorise in this behalf.`
  line `( 2 ) A copy of the annual accounts together with the audit report thereon shall be submitted to the`
  line `Visitor along with the observations of the Executive Council.`
  line `( 3 ) Any observations made by the Visitor on the annual accounts shall be brought to the notice of the`
  line `Executive Council and the views of the Executive Council, if any, on such observation shall be submitted`
  line `to the Visitor.`
  line `( 4 ) A copy of the annual accounts together with the audit report as submitted to the Visitor, shall also`
  line `be submitted to the Central Government, who shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before`
  line `both Houses of Parliament.`
  line `( 5 ) The audited annual accounts after having been laid before both Houses of Parliament shall be`
  line `published in the Gazette of India.`
  line `32. Conditions of service of employees. — ( 1 ) Every employee of the University shall be appointed`
  line `under a written contract, which shall be lodged with the University and a copy of which shall be furnished`
  line `to the employee concerned.`
  line `( 2 ) Any dispute arising out of the contract between the University and any employee shall, at the`
  line `request of the employee, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by`
  line `the Executive Council, one member nominated by the employee and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `( 3 ) The decision of the Tribunal shall be final and no suit shall lie in any civil court in respect of the`
  line `matters decided by the Tribunal.`
  line `( 4 ) Every request made by the employee under sub-section ( 2 ) shall be deemed to be a submission to`
  line `arbitration upon the terms of this section within the meaning of the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940).`
  line `( 5 ) The procedure for regulating the work of the Tribunal shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `33. Procedure of appeal and arbitration in disciplinary cases against students. — ( 1 ) Any student`
  line `or candidate for an examination whose name has been removed from the rolls of the University by the`
  line `orders or resolution of the Vice-Chancellor, Discipline Committee or Examination Committee, as the case`
  line `may be, and who has been debarred from appearing at the examination of the University for more than`
  line `one year, may, within ten days of the date of receipt of such orders or copy of such resolution by him,`
  line `appeal to the Executive Council and the Executive Council may confirm, modify or reverse the decision`
  line `of the Vice-Chancellor or the Committee, as the case may be.`
  line `( 2 ) Any dispute arising out of any disciplinary action taken by the University against a student shall,`
  line `at the request of such student, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration and the provisions of sub-sections`
  line `( 2 ), ( 3 ), ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) of section 32 shall, as far as may be, apply to a reference made under this sub-section.`
  line `34. Right to appeal. — Every employee or student of the University or Institution shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, have a right to appeal within such time as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes, to the Executive Council against the decision of any officer or authority of the`
  line `University or of Institution, as the case may be, and thereupon, the Executive Council may confirm,`
  line `modify or reverse the decision appealed against.`
  line `35. Provident and pension funds. — ( 1 ) The University shall constitute for the benefit of its`
  line `employees such provident fund or pension fund or provide such insurance schemes as it may deem fit in`
  line `such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line `( 2 ) Where such provident fund or pension fund has been so constituted, the Central Government may`
  line `declare that the provision of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925), shall apply to such fund, as if it`
  line `were a Government provident fund.`
  line `36. Disputes as to constitution of University authorities and bodies. — If any question arises as to`
  line `whether any person has been duly elected or appointed as, or is entitled to be, a member of any authority`
  line `or other body of the University, the matter shall be referred to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be`
  line final.
  line `37. Constitution of Committees. — Where any authority of the University is given power by this Act`
  line `or the Statutes to appoint Committees, such Committees shall, save as otherwise provided, consist of the`
  line `members of the authority concerned and of such other person, if any, as the authority in each case may`
  line `think fit.`
  line `38. Filling of casual vacancies. — All casual vacancies among the members (other than ex officio`
  line `members) of any authority or other body of the University shall be filled, as soon as may be, by the`
  line `person or body who appoints, elects or co-opts the member whose place has become vacant and any`
  line `person appointed, elected or co-opted to a casual vacancy shall be a member of such authority or body for`
  line `the residue of the term for which the person whose place he fills would have been a member.`
  line `39. Proceedings of University authorities or bodies not invalidated by vacancies. — No act or`
  line `proceedings of any authority or other body of the University shall be invalid merely by reason of the`
  line `existence of a vacancy or vacancies among its members.`
  line `40. Protection of action taken in good faith. — No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against`
  line `any officer or other employee of the University for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `41. Mode of proof of University record. — A copy of any receipt, application, notice, order,`
  line `proceeding, resolution of any authority or Committee of the University, or other documents in possession`
  line `of the University, or any entry in any register duly maintained by the University, if certified by the`
  line `Registrar, shall be received as prima facie evidence of such receipt, application, notice, order, proceeding,`
  line `resolution or documents or the existence of entry in the register and shall be admitted as evidence of the`
  line `matters and transactions therein where the original thereof would, if produced, have been admissible in`
  line `evidence, notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.`
  line `42. Power to remove difficulties. — ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line `43. Transitional provisions. — Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and the Statutes, —`
  line `( a ) the first Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor and the said officer shall hold office for a`
  line `term of five years;`
  line `( b ) the first Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor in such manner and on such`
  line `conditions as may be deemed fit and the said officer shall hold office for such term, not exceeding`
  line `five years as may be specified by the Visitor;`
  line `( c ) the first Registrar and the first Finance Officer shall be appointed by the Visitor and each of`
  line `the said officers shall hold office for a term of three years;`
  line `( d ) the first Court and the first Executive Council shall consist of not more than thirty members`
  line `and eleven members respectively who shall be nominated by the Visitor and they shall hold office for`
  line `a term of three years;`
  line `( e ) the first Academic Council shall consist of not more than twenty-one members who shall be`
  line `nominated by the Visitor and shall hold office for a term of three years:`
  line `Provided that if any vacancy occurs in the above offices or authorities, the same shall be filled by`
  line `appointment or nomination, as the case may be, by the Visitor, and the person so appointed or`
  line `nominated shall hold office for so long as the officer or member in whose place he is appointed or`
  line `nominated would have held that office, if such vacancy had not occurred.`
  line `44. Statutes, Ordinances and Regulations to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid`
  line `before Parliament. — ( 1 ) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be published`
  line `in the Official Gazette.`
  line `( 2 ) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation or both Houses agree that the Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation should not be made, the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation shall thereafter have`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_13_footnotes:
