obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously down under`
  line `that Statute, Ordinance or Regulation.`
  line `( 3 ) The power to make Statutes Ordinances or Regulations shall include the power to give`
  line `retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the Statutes,`
  line `Ordinances or Regulations or any of them but not retrospective effect shall be given to any Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation so as to prejudicially affect the Interests of any person to whom such Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `THE SCHEDULE`
  line `(See section 27)`
  line `T HE S TATUTES OF THE U NIVERSITY`
  line `The Chancellor`
  line `1. ( 1 ) The Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor from a panel of not less than three persons`
  line `recommended by the Executive Council from amongst persons of eminence in the academic or public life`
  line `of the country:`
  line `Provided that if the Visitor does not approve of any of the persons so recommended he may call for`
  line `fresh recommendations from the Executive Council.`
  line `( 2 ) The Chancellor shall hold office for a term of three years and shall be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line `Provided that notwithstanding the expiry of his term of office, the Chancellor shall continue to hold`
  line `office until his successor enters upon his office.`
  line `The Vice-Chancellor`
  line `2. ( 1 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor from a panel of not less than three`
  line `persons who shall be recommended by a Committee as constituted under clause ( 2 ):`
  line `Provided that if the Visitor does not approve of any of the persons included in the panel, he may call`
  line `for a fresh panel.`
  line `( 2 ) The Committee referred to in clause ( 1 ) shall consist of three persons, none of whom shall be an`
  line `employee of the University or an institution associated with the University, or a member of the Executive`
  line `Council or Academic Council or of any other authority of the University. Out of the three persons, two`
  line `shall be nominated by the Executive Council and one by the Visitor and the nominee of the Visitor shall`
  line `be the convenor of the Committee.`
  line `( 3 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be a whole-time salaried officer of the University.`
  line `( 4 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall hold office for a term of five years from the date on which he enters`
  line `upon his office, and he shall not be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line `Provided that the Visitor may direct any Vice-Chancellor after his term has expired, to continue in`
  line `office for such period, not exceeding a total period of one year, as may be specified by him or till his`
  line `successor is appointed and enters upon his office, whichever is earlier.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( 4 ) a person appointed as Vice-Chancellor shall, if`
  line `he attains the age of sixty-five years during the term of his office or any extension thereof, retire from`
  line office.
  line `( 6 ) The emoluments and other conditions of service of the Vice-Chancellor shall be as follows: —`
  line `( i ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be paid a monthly salary and allowances other than house rent`
  line `allowances at the rates fixed by the Central Government from time to time:`
  line `Provided that if he assumes office after retiring on superannuation from a pensionable post, his`
  line `salary and allowances shall be reduced by the gross amount of his pension prior to commutation or`
  line `the payment of pension shall be held in abeyance until he relinquishes office:`
  line `Provided further that if he assumes office after retiring on superannuation from a non-pensionable`
  line `post, his salary and allowances shall be reduced by the gross amount equivalent of retirement benefits`
  line `availed of by him on superannuation:`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_16:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-16
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Page 16`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `Provided also that where such employee had been a member of any pension scheme, the`
  line `University shall make the necessary contribution to such scheme.`
  line `( ii ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be entitled to use rent free furnished residential accommodation`
  line `maintained by the University.`
  line `( iii ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be entitled to such terminal benefits and allowances as may be`
  line `fixed by the Executive Council with the approval of the Visitor from time to time:`
  line `Provided that where an employee of the University or an Institution or of any other University or`
  line `any college or Institution maintained by or affiliated to such other University, is appointed as the`
  line `Vice-Chancellor he may be allowed to continue to contribute to any provident fund of which he is a`
  line `member and the University shall contribute to the account of such person in that provident fund at the`
  line `same rate at which the person had been contributing immediately before his appointment as the Vice-`
  line `Chancellor:`
  line `Provided further that where such employee had been a member of any pension scheme, the`
  line `University shall make the necessary contribution to such scheme.`
  line `( iv ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be entitled to travelling allowance at such rates as may be fixed by`
  line `the Executive Council.`
  line `( v ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be entitled to leave on full pay at the rate of thirty days in a`
  line `calendar year and the leave shall be credited to his account in advance in two half yearly installments`
  line `of fifteen days each on the 1st day of January and July every year:`
  line `Provided that if the Vice-Chancellor assumes or relinquishes charge of the office of the Vice-`
  line `Chancellor during the currency of a half year the leave shall be credited proportionately at the rate of`
  line `two and-a-half days for each completed month of service.`
  line `( vi ) In addition to the leave referred to in sub-clause ( v ), the Vice-Chancellor shall also be entitled`
  line `to half pay leave at the rate of twenty days for each completed year of service. This half pay leave`
  line `may also be availed of as commuted leave on full pay on medical certificate. When commuted leave`
  line `is availed, twice the amount of half pay leave shall be debited against half pay leave due.`
  line `( 7 ) If the office of the Vice-Chancellor becomes vacant due to death, resignation or otherwise, or if he`
  line `is unable to perform his duties due to ill health or any other cause, the Pro-Vice Chancellor shall perform`
  line `the duties of the Vice-Chancellor.`
  line `Provided that if the Pro-Vice-Chancellor is not available, the senior-most professor shall perform the`
  line `duties of the Vice-Chancellor until a new Vice-Chancellor assumes office or until the existing`
  line `Vice-Chancellor attends to the duties of his office as the case may be.`
  line `Powers and duties of the Vice-Chancellor`
  line `3. ( 1 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be ex officio Chairman of the Executive Council, the Academic`
  line `Council and the Finance Committee and shall in the absence of the Chancellor preside at the convocations`
  line `held for conferring degrees and the meetings of the court.`
  line `( 2 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall be entitled to be present at, and address, any meeting of any authority`
  line `or other body of the University, but shall not be entitled to vote thereat unless he is a member of such`
  line `authority or body.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall be the duty of the Vice-Chancellor to see that this Act, the Statutes, the Ordinances and the`
  line `Regulations are duly observed and he shall have all the powers necessary to ensure such observance.`
  line `( 4 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall exercise control over the affairs of the University and shall give effect`
  line `to the decisions of all the authorities of the University.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_17:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-17
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Page 17`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_17_footnotes
  sourcePage 17
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `( 5 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall have all the powers necessary for the proper maintenance of discipline`
  line `in the University and he may delegate any such powers to such person or persons as he deems fit.`
  line `( 6 ) The Vice-Chancellor shall have the power to convene or cause to be convened the meetings of the`
  line `court, the Executive Council, the Academic Council and the Finance Committee.`
  line Pro-Vice-Chancellor
  line `4. ( 1 ) The Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendation`
  line `of the Vice-Chancellor:`
  line `Provided that where the recommendation of the Vice-Chancellor is not accepted by the Executive`
  line `Council the matter shall be referred to the Visitor who may either appoint the person recommended by the`
  line `Vice-Chancellor or ask the Vice-Chancellor to recommend another person to the Executive Council:`
  line `Provided further that the Executive Council may, on the recommendation of the Vice-Chancellor,`
  line `appoint a Professor to discharge the duties of the Pro-Vice-Chancellor in addition to his own duties as a`
  line Professor.
  line `( 2 ) The term of office of the Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall be such as may be decided by the Executive`
  line `Council but it shall not in any case exceed five years or until the expiration of the term of office of the`
  line `Vice-Chancellor, whichever is earlier:`
  line `Provided that the Pro-Vice-Chancellor whose term of office has expired shall be eligible for`
  line `reappointment:`
  line `Provided further that, in any case, the Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall retire on attaining the age of sixty-`
  line `five years.`
  line `( 3 ) The emoluments and other terms and conditions of service of the Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the Executive Council from time to time.`
  line `( 4 ) The Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall assist the Vice-Chancellor in respect of such matters as may be`
  line `specified by the Vice-Chancellor in this behalf from time to time and shall also exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties as may be assigned or delegated to him by the Vice-Chancellor.`
  line Registrar
  line `5. ( 1 ) The Registrar shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendation of a`
  line `Selection Committee constituted for the purpose and shall be a whole-time salaried officer of the`
  line University.
  line `( 2 ) He shall be appointed for a term of five years and shall be eligible for reappointment.`
  line `( 3 ) The emoluments and other terms and conditions of service of the Registrar shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Executive Council from time to time:`
  line `Provided that the Registrar shall retire on attaining the age of sixty years:`
  line `Provided further that a Registrar shall, notwithstanding his attaining the age of sixty years, continue in`
  line `office until his successor is appointed and enters upon his office or until the expiry of a period of one`
  line `year, whichever is earlier.`
  line `( 4 ) When the office of the Registrar is vacant or when the Registrar is, by reason of illness, absence or`
  line `any other cause, unable to perform the duties of his office, the duties of the officer shall be performed by`
  line `such person as the Vice-Chancellor may appoint for the purpose.`
  line `( 5 ) ( a ) The Registrar shall have power to take disciplinary action against such of the employees, other`
  line `than teachers and academic staff, as may be specified in the Ordinances, to suspend them pending inquiry,`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_18:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-18
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Page 18`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `to administer warnings to them or to impose on them the penalty of censure or the withholding of`
  line `increment:`
  line `Provided that no such penalty shall be imposed unless the person concerned has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed to be taken in regard to him.`
  line `( b ) An appeal shall lie to the Vice-Chancellor against any order of the Registrar imposing any of the`
  line `penalties specified in sub-clause ( a ).`
  line `( c ) In a case where the inquiry discloses that a punishment beyond the power of the Registrar is called`
  line `for, the Registrar shall, upon concluding of the inquiry make a report to the Vice-Chancellor along with`
  line `his recommendations:`
  line `Provided that an appeal shall lie to the Executive Council against an order of the Vice-Chancellor`
  line `imposing any penalty.`
  line `( 6 ) The Registrar shall be ex officio Secretary of the Court, the Executive Council, the Academic`
  line `Council and the Boards of Studies, but shall not be deemed to be a member of any of these authorities.`
  line `( 7 ) It shall be the duty of the Registrar —`
  line `( a ) to be the custodian of the records, the common seal and such other property of the University`
  line `as the Executive Council shall commit to his charges;`
  line `( b ) to issue all notices convening meetings of the Court, the Executive Council, the Academic`
  line `Council, the Boards of Studies and of any Committees appointed by those au thorities;`
  line `( c ) to keep the minutes of all the meetings of the Court, the Executive Council the Academic`
  line `Council and of any Committees appointed by those authorities;`
  line `( d ) to conduct the official correspondence of the Court, the Executive Council and the Academic`
  line Council;
  line `( e ) to arrange for and superintend the examinations of the University in accordance with the`
  line `manner prescribed by the Ordinances;`
  line `( f ) to supply to the Visitor copies of the agenda of the meetings of the authorities of the`
  line `University as soon as they are issued and the minutes of such meetings;`
  line `( g ) to represent the University in suits or proceedings by or against the University, sign`
  line `powers-of-attorney and verify pleadings or depute his representative for the purpose; and`
  line `( h ) to perform such other duties as may be specified in the Statutes, the Ordinances or the`
  line `Regulations or as may be required from time to time by the Executive Council or the`
  line Vice-Chancellor.
  line `The Finance Officer`
  line `6. ( 1 ) The Finance Officer shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendations of a`
  line `Selection Committee constituted for the purpose and he shall be a whole time salaried officer of the`
  line University.
  line `( 2 ) He shall be appointed for a term of five years and shall be eligible for reappointment.`
  line `( 3 ) The emoluments and other terms and conditions of service of the Finance Officer shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Executive Council from time to time:`
  line `Provided that a Finance Officer shall retire on attaining the age of sixty years:`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_19:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-19
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Page 19`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `Provided further that the Finance Officer shall, notwithstanding his attaining the age of sixty years`
  line `continue in office until his successor is appointed and enters upon his office or until the expiry of a period`
  line `of one year whichever is earlier.`
  line `( 4 ) When the office of the Finance Officer is vacant or when the Finance Officer is, by reason of`
  line `illness, absence or any other cause, unable to perform the duties of his office, the duties of the office shall`
  line `be performed by such person as the Vice-Chancellor may appoint for the purpose.`
  line `( 5 ) The Finance Officer shall be ex officio Secretary of the Finance Committee but shall not be`
  line `deemed to be a member of such Committee.`
  line `( 6 ) The Finance Officer shall —`
  line `( a ) exercise general supervision over the funds of the University and shall advise it as regards its`
  line `financial policy; and`
  line `( b ) perform such other financial functions as may be assigned to him by the Executive Council or`
  line `as may be prescribed by the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
  line `( 7 ) Subject to the control of the Executive Council, the Finance Officer shall —`
  line `( a ) hold and manage the property and investments of the University including trust and endowed`
  line property;
  line `( b ) ensure that the limits fixed by the Executive Council for recurring and non-recurring`
  line `expenditure for a year are not exceeded and that all moneys are expended on the purpose for which`
  line `they are granted or allotted;`
  line `( c ) be responsible for the preparation of annual accounts and the budget of the University and for`
  line `their presentation to the Executive Council;`
  line `( d ) keep a constant watch on the state of the cash and bank balances and on the state of`
  line investments;
  line `( e ) watch the progress of the collection of revenue and advise on the methods of collection`
  line employed;
  line `( f ) ensure that the registers of buildings, land, furniture and equipment are maintained up-to-date`
  line `and that stock-checking is conducted, of equipment and other consumable materials in all offices,`
  line `Special Centres, Specialised Laboratories and Institutions;`
  line `( g ) bring to the notice of the Vice-Chancellor unauthorised expenditure and other financial`
  line `irregularities and suggest disciplinary a ction against persons at fault; and`
  line `( h ) call for from any office, Centre, Laboratory or Institution any information or returns that he`
  line `may consider necessary for the performance of his duties.`
  line `( 8 ) Any receipt given by the Finance Officer or the person or persons duly authorised in this behalf by`
  line `the Executive Council for any money payable to the University shall be sufficient discharge for payment`
  line `of such money.`
  line `Deans of Schools of Studies`
  line `7. ( 1 ) Every Dean of a School of Studies shall be appointed by the Vice-Chancellor from among the`
  line `Professors in the School for a period of three years and he shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line `Provided that a Dean on attaining the age of sixty years shall cease to hold office as such:`
  line `Provided further that if at any time there is no Dean in a School, the Vice-Chancellor,`
  line `Pro-Vice-Chancellor or a Dean authorised by the Vice-Chancellor in this behalf, shall exercise the powers`
  line `of the Dean of the School.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_20:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-20
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Page 20`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `( 2 ) When the office of the Dean is vacant or when the Dean is, by reason of illness, absence or any`
  line `other cause, unable to perform duties of his office, the duties of the office shall be performed by such`
  line `person as the Vice-Chancellor may appoint for the purpose.`
  line `( 3 ) The Dean shall be the Head of the School and shall be responsible for the conduct and`
  line `maintenance of the standards of teaching and research in the School and shall have such other functions`
  line `as may be prescribed by the Ordinances.`
  line `( 4 ) The Dean shall have the right to be present and to speak at any meeting of the Board of Studies or`
  line `Committees of the School as the case may be, but shall not have the right to vote thereat unless he is a`
  line `member thereof.`
  line `Heads of Departments`
  line `8. ( 1 ) In the case of Departments which have more than one Professor the Head of the Department`
  line `shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendation of the Vice-Chancellor from among`
  line `the Professors.`
  line `( 2 ) In the case of Departments where there is no Professor or there is only one Professor, the`
  line `Executive Council shall have the option to appoint, on the recommendation of the Vice-Chancellor, either`
  line `the Professor or a Reader as the Head of the Department:`
  line `Provided that it shall be open to a Professor or Reader to decline the offer of appointment as the Head`
  line `of the Department.`
  line `( 3 ) A person appointed as the Head of the Department shall hold office as such for a period of three`
  line `years and shall be eligible for reappointment.`
  line `( 4 ) A Head of a Department may resign his office at any time during his tenure of office.`
  line `( 5 ) A Head of a Department shall perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Ordinances.`
  line Proctor
  line `9. ( 1 ) The Proctor shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendation of the`
  line `Vice-Chancellor and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be assigned to him by`
  line `the Vice-Chancellor.`
  line `( 2 ) The Proctor shall hold office for a term of two years and shall be eligible for reappointment.`
  line Librarian
  line `10. ( 1 ) The Librarian shall be appointed by the Executive Council on the recommendations of the`
  line `Selection Committee constituted for the purpose and shall be a whole-time salaried officer of the`
  line University.
  line `( 2 ) The Librarian shall exercise such powers and perform such duties and shall have such`
  line `emoluments, terms and conditions of service as may be prescribed by the Executive Council.`
  line `The Court`
  line `11. Ten members of the Court shall form a quorum for a meeting of the Court.`
  line `The Executive Council`
  line `12. Five members of the Executive Council shall form a quorum for a meeting of the Executive`
  line Council.
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_21:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-21
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `Powers and functions of the Executive Council`
  line `13. ( 1 ) The Executive Council shall have the power of management and administration of the revenue`
  line `and property of the University and the conduct of all administrative affairs of the University not otherwise`
  line `provided for.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, the Executive Council shall,`
  line `in addition to all other powers vested in it, have the following powers, namely: —`
  line `( i ) to create teaching and academic posts, to determine the number and emoluments of such posts`
  line `and to define the duties and conditions of service of Professors, Readers, Lecturers and other`
  line `academic staff and Principals of Institutions maintained by the University:`
  line `Provided that no action shall be taken by the Executive Council in respect of the number,`
  line `qualifications and the emoluments of teachers and academic staff otherwise than after consideration`
  line `of the recommendations of the Academic Council;`
  line `( ii ) to appoint such Professors, Readers, Lecturers and other academic staff, as may be necessary`
  line `and Principals of Institution maintained by the University on the recommendation of the Selection`
  line `Committee constituted for the purpose and to fill up temporary vacan cies therein;`
  line `( iii ) to create administrative, ministerial and other necessary posts and to make appointments`
  line `thereto in the manner prescribed by the Ordinances;`
  line `( iv ) to grant leave of absence to any officer of the University other than the Chancellor and the`
  line `Vice-Chancellor, and to make necessary arrangements for the discharge of the functions of such`
  line `officer during his absence;`
  line `( v ) to regulate and enforce discipline among employees in accordance with the Statutes and the`
  line Ordinances.
  line `( vi ) to manage and regulate the finances, accounts, investments, property, business and all other`
  line `administrative affairs of the University and for that purpose to appoint such agents as it may think fit;`
  line `( vii ) to fix limits on the total recurring and the total non-recurring expenditure for a year on the`
  line `recommendations of the Finance Committee;`
  line `( viii ) to invest any money belonging to the University, including any unapplied income, in such`
  line `stocks, funds, share or securities, from time to time as it may think fit or in the purchase of`
  line `immovable property in India with the like powers of varying such investment from time to time;`
  line `( ix ) to transfer or accept transfers of any movable or immovable property on behalf of the`
  line University;
  line `( x ) to provide buildings, premises, furniture and apparatus and other means needed for carrying`
  line `on the work of the University;`
  line `( xi ) to enter into, vary, carry o ut and cancel contracts on behalf of the University;`
  line `( xii ) to entertain, adjudicate upon, and if thought fit, to redress any grievances of the employees`
  line `and students of the University who may, for any reason, feel aggrieved;`
  line `( xiii ) to appoint examiners and moderators and, if necessary, to remove them and to fix their fees,`
  line `emoluments and travelling and other allowances, after consulting the Academic Council;`
  line `( xiv ) to select a common seal for the University and provide for the custody a nd use of such seal;`
  line `( xv ) to make such special arrangements as may be necessary for the residence and discipline of`
  line `women students;`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `( xvi ) to delegate any of its powers to the Vice-Chancellor, the Pro-Vice-Chancellor, the Deans,`
  line `the Registrar or the Finance Officer or such other employee or authority of the University or to a`
  line `committee appointed by it as it may deem fit;`
  line `( xvii ) to institute fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line `( xviii ) to provide for inviting Writers-in-Residence and determine the terms and conditions of`
  line `such invitations;`
  line `( xix ) to provide for the appointment of Visiting Profe ssors, Emeritus Professors; Con sultants and`
  line `Scholars and determine the terms and conditions of such appointments; and`
  line `( xx ) to exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed`
  line `on it by the Act, or the Statutes.`
  line `The Academic Council`
  line `14. Ten members of the Academic Council shall form quorum for a meeting of the Academic`
  line Council.
  line `Powers and functions of the Academic Council`
  line `15. Subject to the Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, the Academic Council shall, in addition to all`
  line `other powers vested in it, have the following powers, namely: —`
  line `( a ) to exercise general supervision over the academic policies of the University and to give`
  line `directions regarding methods of instructions, co-ordinating teaching among the Institutions and`
  line `evaluation of research or improvement in academic standards;`
  line `( b ) to bring about inter-School co-ordination, to establish or appoint committees or boards, for`
  line `taking up projects on an inter-School basis;`
  line `( c ) to consider matters of general academic interest either on its own initiative or on a reference`
  line `by a School or the Executive Council and to take appropriate action thereon; and`
  line `( d ) to frame such regulations and rules consistent with the Statutes and the Ordinances regarding`
  line `the academic functioning of the University, discipline, residence, admissions, award of fellowship`
  line `and studentships, fees, concessions, corporate life and attendance.`
  line `Schools of Studies and Departments`
  line `16. ( 1 ) The University shall have the following Schools of Studies, namely: —`
  line `( i ) School of Language;`
  line `( ii ) School of Literature;`
  line `( iii ) School of Culture; and`
  line `( iv ) School of Translation and Interpretation.`
  line `( 2 ) Every School shall have a School Board and the members of the first School Board shall be`
  line `nominated by the Executive Council and shall hold office for a period of three years.`
  line `( 3 ) The powers and functions of a School Board shall be prescribed by the Ordinances.`
  line `( 4 ) The conduct of the meetings of a School Board and the quorum required for such meetings shall`
  line `be prescribed by the Ordinances.`
  line `( 5 ) ( a ) Each School shall consist of such Departments as may be assigned to it by the Ordinances:`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `Provided that the Executive Council may, on the recommendation of the Academic Council, establish`
  line `Centres of Studies to which may be assigned such teachers of the University as the Executive Council`
  line `may consider necessary.`
  line `( b ) Each Department shall consist of the following members, namely: —`
  line `( i ) Teachers of the Department;`
  line `( ii ) persons conducting research in the Department;`
  line `( iii ) Dean of the School;`
  line `( iv ) Honorary Professors, if any, attached to the Department; and`
  line `( v ) such other persons as may be members of the Department in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `the Ordinances.`
  line `17. ( 1 ) Each Department shall have a Board of Studies.`
  line `( 2 ) The constitution of the Board of Studies and the term of office of its members shall be prescribed`
  line `by the Ordinances.`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to the overall control and supervision of the Academic Council, the functions of the Board`
  line `of Studies shall be to approve subjects for research for various degrees and other requirements of research`
  line `degrees and to recommend to the concerned School Board in the manner prescribed by the Ordinances —`
  line `( a ) courses of studies and appointment of examiners for Post-graduate courses, but excluding`
  line `research degrees;`
  line `( b ) appointment of supervisors of research; and`
  line `( c ) measures for the improvement of the standard of post-graduate teaching and research:`
  line `Provided that the above functions of a Board of Studies shall during the period of three years`
  line `immediately after the commencement of the Act, be performed by the Department.`
  line `Finance Committee`
  line `18. ( 1 ) The Finance Committee shall consist of the following members, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the Vice- Chancellor;`
  line `( ii ) the Pro-Vice- Chancellor;`
  line `( iii ) three persons nominated by the Executive Council, out of whom at least one shall be a`
  line `member of the Executive Council; and`
  line `( iv ) three persons nominated by the Visitor.`
  line `( 2 ) Five members of the Finance Committee shall form a quorum for a meeting of the Finance`
  line Committee.
  line `( 3 ) All the members of the Finance Committee other than ex officio members, shall hold office for a`
  line `term of three years.`
  line `( 4 ) The Finance Committee shall meet at least twice every year to examine the accounts and to`
  line `scrutinise proposals for expenditure.`
  line `( 5 ) All proposals relating to creation of posts, and those items which have not been included in the`
  line `Budget should be examined by the Finance Committee for consideration and comments and thereafter`
  line `submitted to the Executive Council.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_24:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-24
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `( 6 ) The annual accounts and the financial estimates of the University prepared by the Finance Officer`
  line `shall be laid before the Finance Committee for consideration and comments and thereafter submitted to`
  line `the Executive Council for approval.`
  line `( 7 ) The Finance Committee shall recommend limits for the total recurring expenditure and the total`
  line `non-recurring expenditure for the year, based on the income and resources of the University (which in the`
  line `case of productive works, may include the proceeds of loans).`
  line `Selection Committees`
  line `19. ( 1 ) There shall be Selection Committees for making recommendations to the Executive Council`
  line `for appointment to the posts of Professor, Reader, Lecturer, Registrar, Finance Officer, Librarian and`
  line `Principals of Institutions.`
  line `( 2 ) The Selection Committee for appointment to the posts specified in column 1 of the Table shall`
  line `consist of the Vice-Chancellor, Pro-Vice-Chancellor, a nominee of the Visitor and the persons specified`
  line `in the corresponding entry in column 2 of the said Table: —`
  line `T ABLE`
  line `1 2`
  line `Professor ( i ) The Dean of the School concerned.`
  line `( ii ) The Head of the Department concerned`
  line `if he is a Professor.`
  line `( iii ) Three persons not in the service of the`
  line `University, nominated by the Executive`
  line `Council, out of a panel of names recom-`
  line `mended by the Academic Council for`
  line `their special knowledge of, or interest`
  line `in, the subject with which the Professor`
  line `will be concerned.`
  line `Reader/Lecturer ( i ) The Dean of the School concerned.`
  line `( ii ) The Head of the Department concerned.`
  line `( iii ) Two persons not in the service of the`
  line `University, nominated by the Executive`
  line `Council, out of a panel of names`
  line `recommended by the Academic Council`
  line `for their special knowledge of, or`
  line `interest in, the subject with which the`
  line `Reader or a Lecturer will be concerned.`
  line `Registrar, Finance Officer ( i ) Two members of the Executive Council`
  line `nominated by it.`
  line `( ii ) One person not in the service of the`
  line `University nominated by the Executive`
  line Council.
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_25:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-25
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Page 25`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `1 2`
  line `Librarian ( i ) Two persons not in the service of the`
  line `University, who have special`
  line `knowledge of the subject of the Library`
  line `Science/Library Administration to be`
  line `nominated b y the Executive Council.`
  line `( ii ) One person not in the service of the`
  line `University, nominated by the Executive`
  line Council.
  line `Head of the Institution Three persons not in the service of the`
  line `University of whom two shall be nomi -`
  line `nated and one by the Academic Council`
  line `for thei r special by the Executive`
  line `Coun cil knowledge of, or interest in, a`
  line `subject in which instruction is being`
  line `provided by the Institution.`
  line `Note: 1. Where the appointment is being made for an int er - disciplinary project, the head of the project shall be`
  line `deemed to be the Head of the Department concerned.`
  line `2. The Professor to be nominated shall be Professor concerned with the speciality for which the selection is`
  line `being made and that the V ice - Chancellor shall consult the Head of the Department and the Dean of School`
  line `before nominating the Professor.`
  line `( 3 ) The Vice-Chancellor, or in his absence, the Pro-Vice-Chancellor shall preside the meetings of a`
  line `Selection Committee:`
  line `Provided that the meetings of the Selection Committee shall be fixed after prior consultation with the`
  line `subject to the convenience of Visitor's nominee and the persons nominated by the Executive Council`
  line `under clause ( 2 ):`
  line `Provided further that the proceedings of the Selection Committee shall not be valid unless —`
  line `( a ) where the number of Visitor's nominee and the persons nominated by the Executive Council is`
  line `four in all, at least three of them attend the meeting; and`
  line `( b ) where the number of Visitor's nominee and the persons nominated by the Executive Council is`
  line `three in all, at least two of them attend the meeting.`
  line `( 4 ) The meeting of Selection Committee shall be convened by the Vice-Chancellor or in his absence`
  line `by the Pro-Vice-Chancellor.`
  line `( 5 ) The procedure to be followed by a Selection Committee in making recommendations shall be laid`
  line `down in the Ordinances.`
  line `( 6 ) If the Executive Council is unable to accept the recommendations made by a Selection`
  line `Committee, it shall record its reasons and submit the case to the Visitor for final orders.`
  line `( 7 ) Appointments to temporary posts shall be made in the manner indicated below:`
  line `( i ) if the temporary vacancy is for a duration longer than one academic session, it shall he filled`
  line `on the advice of the Selection Committee in accordance with the procedure indicated in the foregoing`
  line `clauses:`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_26:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-26
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Page 26`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_26_footnotes
  sourcePage 26
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_26_content:
  string
  line 26
  line `Provided that if the Vice-Chancellor is satisfied that in the interest of work it is necessary to fill the`
  line `vacancy, the appointment may be made on a purely temporary basis by a local Selection Committee`
  line `referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) for a period not exceeding six months;`
  line `( ii ) if the temporary vacancy is for a period less than one year, an appointment to such vacancy`
  line `shall be made on the recommendation of a local Selection Committee consisting of the Dean of the`
  line `School concerned, the Head of the Department and a nominee of the Vice-Chancellor:`
  line `Provided that if the same person holds the offices of the Dean and the Head of the Department, the`
  line `Selection Committee may contain two nominees of the Vice-Chancellor:`
  line `Provided further that in case sudden vacancies of teaching posts caused by death or any other reasons,`
  line `the Dean may, in consultation with the Head of the Department concerned make a temporary appointment`
  line `for a month and report to the Vice-Chancellor and the Registrar about such appointment;`
  line `( iii ) no teacher appointed temporarily shall, if he is not recommended by a regular Selection`
  line `Committee for appointment under the Statutes, be continued in service on such temporary`
  line `employment, unless he is subsequently selected by a local Selection Committee of a regular Selection`
  line `Committee, for a temporary or permanent appointment, as the case may be.`
  line `Special mode of appointment`
  line `20. ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in Statute 19, the Executive Council may invite a person`
  line `of high academic distinction and professional attainments to accept a post of Professor or Reader or any`
  line `other academic post in the University, as the case may be, on such terms and conditions as it deems fit,`
  line `and on the person agreeing to do so appoint him to the post.`
  line `( 2 ) The Executive Council may appoint a teacher or any other academic staff working in any other`
  line `University or organisation for undertaking a joint project in accordance with the manner laid down in the`
  line Ordinances.
  line `Appointment for a fixed tenure`
  line `21. The Executive Council may appoint a person selected in accordance with procedure laid down in`
  line `Statute 19 for a fixed tenure on such terms and conditions as it deems fit.`
  line Committees
  line `22. ( 1 ) Any authority of the University may appoint as many standing or special Committees as it`
  line `may deem fit, and may appoint to such Committees persons who are not members of such authority.`
  line `( 2 ) Any such Committees appointed under clause ( 1 ) may deal with any subject delegated to it subject`
  line `to subsequent confirmation by the authority appointing.`
  line `Terms and conditions of service and code of conduct of the teachers, etc`
  line `23. ( 1 ) All the teachers and other academic staff of the University shall, in the absence of any`
  line `agreement to the contrary, be governed by the terms and conditions of service and code of conduct as are`
  line `specified in the Statutes, the Ordinances and the Regulations.`
  line `( 2 ) Every teacher and member of the academic staff of the University shall be appointed on a written`
  line `contract, the form of which shall be prescribed by the Ordinances.`
  line `( 3 ) A copy of every contract referred to in clause ( 2 ) shall be deposited with the Registrar.`
  line `Terms and conditions of service and code of conduct of other employees`
  line `24. All the employees of the University other than the teachers and other academic staff of the`
  line `University, shall in the absence of any contract to the contrary, be governed by the terms and conditions`
  line `of service and code of conduct as are specified in the statutes, the Ordinances and the Regulations.`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_27:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-27
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Page 27`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_27_footnotes
  sourcePage 27
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_27_content:
  string
  line 27
  line `Seniority list`
  line `25. ( 1 ) Whenever, in accordance with the Statutes, any person is to hold an office or be a member of`
  line `an authority of the University by rotation according to seniority, such seniority shall be determined`
  line `according to the length of continuous service of such person in his grade and in accordance with such`
  line `other principles as the Executive Council may frame from time to time.`
  line `( 2 ) It shall be the duty of the Registrar to prepare and maintain in respect of each class of persons to`
  line `whom the provisions of these Statutes apply a complete and up-to-date seniority list in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of clause ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) If two or more persons have equal length of continuous service in a particular grade or the relative`
  line `seniority of any person or persons is otherwise in doubt, the Registrar may on his own motion and shall at`
  line `the request of any such person submit the matter to the Executive Council whose decision thereon shall be`
  line final.
  line `Removal of employees of the University`
  line `26. ( 1 ) Where there is an allegation of misconduct against a teacher, a member of the academic staff`
  line `or other employee of the University, the Vice-Chancellor in the case of the teacher or member of the`
  line `academic staff and the authority competent to appoint (hereinafter referred to as the appointing authority)`
  line `in the case of other employee may, by order in writing place such teacher, member of the academic staff`
  line `or other employee, as the case may be, under suspension and shall forthwith report to the Executive`
  line `Council the circumstances in which the order was made:`
  line `Provided that the Executive Council may, if it is of the opinion that the circumstances or the case do`
  line `not warrant the suspension of the teacher or a member of the academic staff, revoke such order.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the terms of the contract of appointment or of any other`
  line `terms and conditions of service of the employee, the Executive Council in respect of teachers and other`
  line `academic staff, and the appointing authority, in respect of other employees, shall have the power to`
  line `remove a teacher or a member of the academic staff, or as the case may be, other employee on ground of`
  line misconduct.
  line `( 3 ) Save as aforesaid, the Executive Council or as the case may be, the appointing authority shall not`
  line `be entitled to remove any teacher, member of the academic staff or other employee except for a good`
  line `cause and after giving three months notice or on payment of three months salary in lieu thereof.`
  line `( 4 ) No teacher, member of the academic staff or other employee shall be removed under clause ( 2 ) or`
  line `clause ( 3 ) unless he has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed`
  line `to be taken in regard to him.`
  line `( 5 ) The removal of a teacher, member of the academic staff or other employee shall take effect from`
  line `the date on which the order of removal is made:`
  line `Provided that where the teacher, member of the academic staff or other employee is under suspension`
  line `at the time of his removal, such removal shall take effect from the date on which he was placed under`
  line suspension.
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this Statute, a teacher, member`
  line `of the academic staff or other employee may resign, —`
  line `( a ) if he is a permanent employee, only after giving three months' notice in writing to the`
  line `Executive Council or the appointing authority, as the case may be, or by paying three months' salary`
  line `in lieu thereof;`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_28:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-28
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Page 28`
  content obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_28_footnotes
  sourcePage 28
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_28_content:
  string
  line 28
  line `( b ) if he is not a permanent employee, only after giving one month's notice in writing to the`
  line `Executive Council or, as the case may be, the appointing authority or by paying one month's salary in`
  line `lieu thereof:`
  line `Provided that such resignation shall take effect only on the date on which the resignation is accepted`
  line `by the Executive Council or the appointing authority, as the case may be.`
  line `Honorary degrees`
  line `27. ( 1 ) The Executive Council may, on the recommendation of the Academic Council and by a`
  line `resolution passed by a majority of not less than two-thirds of the members present and voting, make`
  line `proposals to the Visitor for the conferment of honorary degrees:`
  line `Provided that in case of emergency the Executive Council may on its own motion, make such`
  line proposals.
  line `( 2 ) The Executive Council may, by a resolution passed by a majority of not less than two-thirds of the`
  line `members present and voting, withdraw, with the previous sanction of the Visitor, any honorary degree`
  line `conferred by the University.`
  line `Withdrawal of degrees, etc.`
  line `28. The Executive Council may, by a special resolution passed by a majority of not less than two-`
  line `thirds of the members present and voting, withdraw any degree or academic distinction conferred on, or`
  line `any certificate or diploma granted to, any person by the University for good and sufficient cause:`
  line `Provided that no such resolution shall be passed until a notice in writing has been given to that person`
  line `calling upon him to show cause within such time as may be specified in the notice why such a resolution`
  line `should not be passed and until his objections, if any, and any evidence he may produce in support of`
  line `them, have been considered by the Executive Council.`
  line `Maintenance of discipline among students of the University`
  line `29. ( 1 ) All powers relating to discipline and disciplinary action in relation to students of the`
  line `University shall vest in the Vice-Chancellor.`
  line `( 2 ) The Vice-Chancellor may delegate all or any of his powers as he deems proper to a Proctor and to`
  line `such other officers as he may specify in this behalf.`
  line `( 3 ) Without prejudice to the generality of his powers relating to the maintenance of discipline, and`
  line `taking such action as may seem to him appropriate for the maintenance of discipline, the Vice-Chancellor`
  line `may, in exercise of his powers, by order, direct that any student or students be expelled, or rusticated, for`
  line `specific period, or be not admitted to a course or courses of study in an Institution or Department of the`
  line `University for stated period, or be punished with fine for an amount to be specified in the order, or be`
  line `debarred from taking an examination or examinations conducted by the University, Institution or`
  line `Department or a School for one or more years, or that the results of the student or students concerned in`
  line `the examination or examinations in which he or they have appeared be cancelled.`
  line `( 4 ) The Heads of Institutions, Deans of Schools of Studies and Heads of teaching Departments in the`
  line `University shall have the authority to exercise all such powers over the students in their respective`
  line `Institutions, Schools and teaching Departments as may be necessary for the proper conduct of such`
  line `Institutions, Schools and teaching Departments.`
  line `( 5 ) Without prejudice to the powers of the Vice-Chancellor, and other persons specified in clause ( 4 ),`
  line `detailed rules of discipline and proper conduct shall be made by the University. The Principals of`
  line `Institutions, Deans of Schools of Studies and Heads of teaching Departments in the University may also`
  line `make the supplementary rules as they deem necessary for the aforesaid purposes.`
