  sourcePage 29
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_29_content:
  string
  line 29
  line Convocations
  line `30. Convocations of the University for the conferring of degrees or for other purposes shall be held in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed by the Ordinances.`
  line `Acting Chairman of meetings`
  line `31. Where no provision is made for a President or Chairman to preside over a meeting of any`
  line `authority of the University or any Committee of such authority or when the President or Chairman so`
  line `provided for is absent, the members present shall elect one from among themselves to preside at such`
  line meeting.
  line Resignation
  line `32. Any member other than an ex officio member, of the Court, the Executive Council, the Academic`
  line `Council or any other authority of the University or any Committee of such authority may resign by letter`
  line `addressed to the Registrar and the resignation shall take effect as soon as such letter is received by the`
  line Registrar.
  line Disqualification
  line `33. ( 1 ) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen as, and for being a member of any of the`
  line `authorities of the university: —`
  line `( i ) if he is of unsound mind;`
  line `( ii ) if he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line `( iii ) if he has been convicted by a court of law of an offence involving moral turpitude and`
  line `sentenced in respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months.`
  line `( 2 ) If any question arises as to whether a person is or had been subjected to any of the`
  line `disqualifications mentioned in clause ( 1 ), the question shall be referred to the Visitor and his decision`
  line `shall be final and no suit or other proceeding shall lie in any civil court against such decision.`
  line `Residence condition for membership and office`
  line `34. Notwithstanding anything contained in the Statutes, a person who is not ordinarily resident in`
  line `India shall not be eligible to be an officer of the University or a member of any authority of the`
  line University.
  line `Membership of authorities by virtue of membership of other bodies`
  line `35. Notwithstanding anything contained in the Statutes, a person who holds any post in the University`
  line `or is a member of any authority or body of the University in his capacity as a member of a particular`
  line `authority or body or as the holder of a particular appointment shall hold such office or membership only`
  line `for so long as he continues to be a member of that particular authority or body or the holder of that`
  line `particular appointment, as the case may be.`
  line `Ordinances how made`
  line `36. ( 1 ) The first Ordinances made under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 28 may be amended, repealed or`
  line `added to at any time by the Executive Council in the manner specified below.`
  line `( 2 ) No Ordinance in respect of the matters enumerated in section 28, other than the one enumerated in`
  line `clause ( m ) of sub-section ( 1 ) thereof, shall be made by the Executive Council unless a draft of such`
  line `Ordinance has been proposed by the Academic Council.`
  line `( 3 ) The Executive Council shall not have power to amend any draft of any Ordinance proposed by the`
  line `Academic Council under clause ( 2 ) but may reject the proposal or return the draft to the Academic`
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
