  sourcePage 30
obj_root_law_translations_hi_sections_30_content:
  string
  line 30
  line `Council for re-consideration either in whole or in part, together with any amendment which the Executive`
  line `Council may suggest.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the Executive Council has rejected or returned the draft of an Ordinance proposed by the`
  line `Academic Council, the Academic Council may consider the question afresh and in case the original draft`
  line `is reaffirmed by a majority of not less than two-thirds of the members present and voting and more than`
  line `half the total number of members of the Academic Council, the draft may be sent back to the Executive`
  line `Council which shall either adopt it or refer it to the Visitor whose decision shall be final.`
  line `( 5 ) Every Ordinance made by the Executive Council shall come into effect immediately.`
  line `( 6 ) Every Ordinance made by the Executive Council shall be submitted to the Visitor within two`
  line `weeks from the date of its adoption. The Visitor shall have the power to direct the University within four`
  line `weeks of the receipt of the Ordinance to suspend the operation of any such Ordinance and he shall, as`
  line `soon as possible, inform the Executive Council about his objection to the proposed Ordinance. The`
  line `Visitor may, after receiving the comments of the University, either withdraw the order suspending the`
  line `Ordinance or disallow the Ordinance and his decision shall be final.`
  line Regulations
  line `37. ( 1 ) The authorities of the University may make Regulations consistent with the Act, the Statutes`
  line `and the Ordinances for the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( i ) laying down the procedure to be observed at their meetings and the number of members`
  line `required to form a quorum;`
  line `( ii ) providing for all matters which are required by the Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances to be`
  line `prescribed by Regulations;`
  line `( iii ) providing for all other matters solely concerning such authorities or committees appointed by`
  line `them and not provided for by the Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
  line `( 2 ) Every authority of the University shall make Regulations providing for the giving of notice to the`
  line `members of such authority of the dates of meeting and of the business to be considered at meetings and`
  line `for the keeping of a record of the proceeding of meetings.`
  line `( 3 ) The Executive Council may direct the amendment in such manner as it may specify of any`
  line `Regulation made under the Statutes or the annulment of any such Regulation.`
  line `Delegation of powers`
  line `38. Subject to the provisions of the Act and the Statutes any officer or authority of the University may`
  line `delegate his or its powers to any other officer or authority or person under his or its respective control and`
  line `subject to the condition that overall responsibility for the exercise of the powers so delegated shall`
  line `continue to vest in the officer or authority delegating such powers.`
